uiConfig.queryString: 'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Event Object Logs' | timestats count as logrecords by 'Event Type' | sort -logrecords

'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Node Object Logs' | link Node, 'Ready Status' | stats latest('Disk Pressure Status') as 'Disk Pressure', latest('Memory Pressure Status') as 'Memory Pressure', latest('PID Pressure Status') as 'PID Pressure', latest('Pods Allocatable') as 'Pods Allocatable', latest('Pods Capacity') as 'Pods Capacity' | fields 'End Time' as 'Last Reported', Count as Records

'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Deployment Object Logs' | stats latest(Namespace) as Namespace, latest('Progressing Status') as Progressing, latest('Available Status') as Available, latest(Replicas) as 'Desired Replicas', latest('Ready Replicas') as 'Ready Replicas', latest('Available Replicas') as 'Available Replicas' by Deployment
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Container Status Logs' or 'Log Source' like 'Kubernetes %Object% Logs' | stats count as logrecords by 'Log Source'
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Pod Object Logs' and 'Pod Phase' = running | timestats span = 15minute distinctcount(Pod) as 'Pods Running' by Node
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Pod Object Logs' and 'Pod Phase' = running | stats latest('Pod Phase') by Pod
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes ReplicaSet Object Logs' | stats latest(Replicas) as Desired, latest('Ready Replicas') as Ready by ReplicaSet

'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Deployment Object Logs' | link Deployment | stats latest('Available Status') as Availability | highlightgroups color = red [ * | where Availability = false ] as NA | highlightgroups color = green [ * | where Availability = true ] as available | fields 'End Time' as 'Last Reported', Count as Records
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Event Object Logs' | stats count as logrecords by Reason | sort -logrecords
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes DaemonSet Object Logs' | stats latest('Desired Scheduled') as Desired, latest('Ready Count') as Ready, latest('Current Scheduled') as 'Current Scheduled' by DaemonSet

'Log Source' in ('Linux Syslog Logs', 'Linux Secure Logs', 'Linux Cron Logs', 'Linux Mail Delivery Logs', 'Linux YUM Logs', 'Ksplice Logs', 'Linux Audit Logs') | stats count as logrecords by 'Log Source' | sort -logrecords

'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes DaemonSet Object Logs' | stats latest(Namespace) as Namespace, latest('Desired Scheduled') as Desired, latest('Current Scheduled') as Scheduled, latest('Ready Count') as Ready, latest(Misscheduled) as Misscheduled by DaemonSet
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Namespace Object Logs' | stats latest(Status) by Namespace
'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Node Object Logs' and 'Ready Status' = true | stats latest('Ready Status') as 'Worker Nodes' by Node

'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes Pod Object Logs' | link Pod | stats latest('Pod Phase') as Status, latest(Node), latest('Controller Kind') as Controller | fields Count as Records, 'End Time' as 'Last Reported' | highlightgroups color = green [ * | where Status in (running, succeeded) ] as healthy | highlightgroups color = red [ * | where Status in (pending, failed) ] as warning

'Log Source' = 'Kubernetes ReplicaSet Object Logs' | stats latest(Namespace) as Namespace, latest('Controller Kind') as 'Controller Kind', latest(Controller) as Controller, latest(Replicas) as 'Desired Replicas', latest('Ready Replicas') as 'Ready Replicas', latest('Available Replicas') as 'Available Replicas' by ReplicaSet
